abstracts.cdata!:
The Sixth Highway Project comprises: (a)
            the construction of 397 km of gravel-surfaced, all-weather
            roads; (b) participation in a program to procure maintenance
            equipment for the EHA; (c) provision of training to the EHA;
            (d) procurement of weighbridges for, a provision of
            technical assistance to the Road Transport Administration
            (RTA); (e) establishment of an organization to develop and
            maintain rural roads; and (f) extension of a subloan to an
            Ethiopian road contractor for the procurement of
            construction equipment.
